  "text": "Skeletal metastases are a common problem in the management of breast cancer patients. Many such patients suffer from bone pain and about one-third of patients with bone metastases develop one or more complications, for example, hypercalcaemia, pathological fractures or spinal cord compression [CITATION_1] . Metastatic breast cancer is incurable but its associated morbidity deserves attention. Understanding the processes involved in metastasis to bone could lead to optimal management of metastatic bone disease.",
